 seconds. YouTube long-form: 8–12 minutes. Shorter often performs better; pad only if content genuinely justifies length.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What video codec should I use for all platforms?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"H.264 (AVC) is universal and reliable across all platforms. VP9 is supported by YouTube but not required. Avoid ProRes or DNxHD for export; use those as master formats and transcode to H.264 at 5–8 Mbps for social upload.\"}}]}]}"}></script>
